  "read": "This is a diagnostic lower-bound for the compressed prefix route, not a production sparse MLA backward. In default mode it materializes [B,H,S,K] scores/probs; in --seq-chunk mode it streams token chunks to bound that slab. The bmm accumulation mode computes the two compressed dKV terms as batched KxS @ SxD GEMMs over heads, then sums the head-local gradients. The flat_gemm mode reshapes heads and tokens into HS rows and computes larger Kx(HS) @ (HS)xD GEMMs that reduce heads directly. The goal is to test whether MFMA-friendly accumulation can beat the query-major per-row atomic dKV path before writing a fused streaming/bucketed kernel.",
